caption: If you haven’t visit this place than it’s a MOST!!! Awesome food and taste... no wonder why it has a 4.7 rating... should have a 5 though... simply awesome!!!!
This restaurant offers superb service and enjoyable menu. One of my favourite restaurants ever. The food and drinks served rapidly and the prices are inexpensive. Recommended.
Great tasting Ramen! Be careful if on a low sodium diet as they are very salty. If you appreciate the review, please "like" it.

If you think ramen is just something collage kids eat think again this place was  awsome I had a ramen dish with pork eggs and veggies is a spicey meso broth and it was delicious and my wife had curry chicken witch was also vary good and for an appetizer we had beef dumplings that were some of the best I've ever had will deffantly be going back

This is my 2nd visit to Tsunami and we were as satisfied this time as much as the last. I tried the "octopus balls" ( bet you didn't know octopus had them, huh?!!!) as this was a favorite for me in Japan. They were very good, the Tsunami ramen was delicious and I couldn't pass getting the croissant bread pudding again!
Just ordered delivery and I got ramen and kimchi. The ramen was insanity! It was the best ramen I've ever had. And the kimchi was pretty good as well. Going to be visiting in person soon.
Yummy
So good omg

The place has a very interesting twist in design. The food is simple but I would probably come back in least twice a week if I lived here in Frederick. I was so hungry that completely forgot to take pictures of my food! Everything was super tasty. The waiter was friendly and did give his recommendations which was pleasant.
They offer a vast variety of fresh food. I enjoyed dining here. Employees are always very kind, prices are affordable and the spot is always well organised.
Great ramen with delicious broth.
Wow nice place to enjoy Ramen

This restaurant was phenomenal. We went in and they didn't waste any time having us seated. We were immediately given menus and not long after we had a waiter ready to take our order. The appetizer was great we went for the Chicken Karaage and I definitely recommend it. I got the Karaage Curry  rice bowl which I recommend again. Anyways customer service was great and so was the food!

I've always hated the fact that it was a 45-60 minute drive from my house to get a good authentic bowl of Ramen. Now, blessedly 10 minutes away is this delightful spot right in the historical downtown of Frederick. Excellent, Tonkatsu and Shoryu with spicy variants with authentic appetizers as well. The space is cozy and quiet. Also, there is a good selection of sake, beer & wine. Definitely worth a trip.
Great menu!! Perfect amount of options. Delicious appetizers and ramen.
Fabulous food, we will definitely be going back for date nights and take out too.
Great service, amazing food.

I got the red curry ramen with chicken instead of pork and couldn’t stop eating it! My brother loved his veggie ramen as well. Also, the Thai bubble tea was incredible. Kate was a nice server. I’ll definitely be back soon! And I would definitely bring visitors to Frederick here if ramen was their thing!  Update: went here three days later craving their red curry ramen and it was just as good carried out as it was to dine in. The customer service was fantastic both times. My boyfriend loved his beef dumplings and chicken tacos. Can’t recommend this place enough!
SO GOOD EVERY TIME! and the food comes out pretty quickly. i ordered pickup once and they separated the noodles and the broth so that the noodles didnt get soggy :)
Beautiful ambiance combined with exceptional customer service. Ramen was delicious! Highly recommend.

First time eating here and the food was terrific. My husband got the Ramen and he loved it. I got a rice dish and it was very good. We also got a appetizer and that was also very good. Perfect place for downtown Frederick.
This is my first time I visit here with my family .  Tonkotsu ramen taste really good and the customer service was great 👍🏻. I will back here when I have chance
This was my first visit and the food was delicious!! The service was also pleasant.  I would go there again.

Love this place, eaten here twice now. Had Tsunami and the spicy miso, both 5/5. Very flavorful soup, good mix of toppings and choices. Overall awesome experience for both food and atmosphere! Definitely check this place out!
DELICIOUS!!
Great ramen! Hard to choose between here and Lazyfish everytime!
Delicious food and reasonably priced! We had the satay tacos, bulgogi tacos and red curry ramen. All were great! Will definitely be coming back.
Delicious Japanese restaurant downtown Frederick.
The ramen we had was very great i like the atmosphere of the restraut 9/10 would go again
Great food they just have a tendency to get orders wrong. One day someone who hates spicy will get a spicy tonkatsu after asking for a normal one
Really good food. We've eaten here a couple of times and everything was amazing each visit.  The Red Curry Ramen is absolutely delicious and so flavorful.  Definitely recommend!

This was my second time there with my girlfriend, because our first time was excellent. However, this visit was only ok. Our server didn't pay much attention to us and the poached egg in my karage bowl was extremely cold and overcooked
Delicious!! Our favorite is the Spicy Miso!! Highly recommended!
Delicious Tsunami rice bowl with pork
Spicy and horrible
Great flavor combinations,excellent service and reasonably priced.Winning!
Awesome food! Love the ramen

Spicy shoyu and tonkatsu are awesome here. If you're used to traditional Ramen these are smaller portions and lack some traditional ingredients but very tasty. The lunch specials are also great. Definitely the best Ramen in Frederick.

The ramen was full of flavor and a perfect portion.  I had the Spicy Tonkatsu Ramen and while it was spicy and had heat, it went away fairly quickly.  The pork was not dry and the menma was surprisingly delicious.  Definitely coming back.
Staff was excellent and food was great.  Will definitely be back again.
Excellent ramen, service, and experience. Found our new eating spot when we visit Frederick

Modern atmosphere, comfortable seating. Ramen wise, it was inexpensive. I ordered spicy miso ramen. Note: make sure you like spicy food. The spice was so powerful, it dulled the ramen broth, so it didn't taste as well as it could have. I will try again, just not with any spice next time. Overall, good experience.
The ramen is amazing. The takoyaki is also good but the serving size is disappointing.
All I have to say is YUMMMM
Fantastic authentic ramen and great selection of japanese brews.
Absolutely a spot worth visiting, the food is good and well prepared, the rates are convenient and it is regularly neat in here. Fantastic work.
Great little place with nice outdoor seating, eat local, buy local

The service was not the best. I don't eat runny eggs (period) so I asked for my eggs to cooked a little more & th waitress had the chef come out to explain why he couldn't cook eggs a little longer. He did it, but he acted like he didn't want to. I didn't & still don't fully understand. Unsure if I'd return.
Ordered Uber eats tonight and the food was wonderful. It was very flavorful with the perfect amount of heat/spice. Very good value for the amount of food you receive.

This was a fantastic experience! The ramen (Red Curry) had such a very fine relaxing mix of flavors which each complimented each other. The Takoyaki appetizer was amazing. The inside is very futuristic and colorful while also being modern and cultured. The staff were very friendly and welcoming and the ramen took barely any time to come out after the amazing Takoyaki.
I really like their authenticity with ramen. However I asked for no poached egg but they still prepared dish with it. Everything else was delicious .

Ordered ramen and shrimp today thru Uber eats and it came really fast!  The shrimp were a tad overcooked but still really great.  The ramen was out of this world good.  I added a little spice to it and it really was great.  If your looking for a newer place to try in Frederick check this place out!
Excellent
Great food great drinks
Comfortable, unique, and most importantly delicious
Delicious Asian Tappas! Never had that before.

I don't normally give low ratings to any restaurant. I also don't expect authentic food from restaurants but this one was a bit bad. My order was wrong and honestly, that doesn't bother me. I ordered a Karaage Bowl and received a Karaage Curry Bowl instead. Didn't care and wanted to eat... until I realized that the Karaage texture was off.  The curry was fine.... after a few more bites... I realized something... it was Orange Chicken... covered in curry. The more I ate, the more Orange Chicken I tasted...  I'm actually quite disappointed. It's fine if it was an attempt at actual Karaage Curry but to use Orange Chicken as a substitute is just insanely embarrassing. This was my first time ordering from this place... and I won't be ordering from this place anymore.
Awsome place to eat some Ramen.

Everything was really great.  The takoyaki was cooked perfectly.  The chashu pork un the ramen melted in your mouth.  The ramen was loaded with toppings rather than too much broth.  The only negative I can realy give is the spoons they provide are ladles.  My hand on the end of the spoon was above my head when I tried to eat the broth. Other than that small issue, great new place in downtown!

The restaurant was very modern looking it was very comforting. The music playing in the background made me dance while eating the absolutely delicious food that was served. Very affordable as well and perfect if you want to share with friends! :D  Ps. Staff were so nice and welcoming. They always made sure we were okay with everything.
Some of the best ramen you'll ever eat. So glad I am about to move closer.
It's nice to have a good ramen shop in Frederick. I had the veggie ramen, and it was delicious.
Anazing ramen!! I recommend the Spicy Miso. Flavor. Worth the price for sure, and the surrounding area makes for a whole dining out experience
The bang bang shrimp is one of the best things I’ve ever had!
Best noodles in the area
Tsunami, please never stop your Bubble Tea. It's awesome. It was one thing I missed when I moved here.

We've picked up takeout twice recently. The ramen is pretty good (spicy tonkatsu) and the service was quick and friendly. Generous portions allow for leftovers for lunch the next day, which is nice. It's not "blown away delicious" but I'll be back for more.
Amazing ramen place! Extremely flavorful food with good options to choose from. There is even vegan ramen with kale noodles.

Went to Tsunami last night for the first time and I must say...it was AH-MAZING! We wanted to eat outside, but that wait was long so we ventured inside. Glad we did! The atmosphere was great, the people were even better. Now let’s talk food! Ok, the Bang Bang Shrimp was so good that I ate the greens after the shrimp was gone. I never do that. It was light and not drenched in sauce. I ordered the Red Curry Ramen. OMG!! Everything about it was PERFECT. The egg was cooked just right. I will not even discuss the croissant bread pudding...just go and try it! I will definitely be back!!
First time visiting Tsunami and I was impressed, had the Chasudon for lunch and loved it. Very well done 👍

I would give 100 stars if I could. My boyfriend's family and I ate there last night. Our group of 6 sat down and ordered about 20 minutes before they closed at 830. However, the entire time we were there we never felt rushed or felt like we were causing a problem. The staff that worked that night was just the greatest I can not thank them enough. Not only was the staff great but the food was amazing too. Just really good ramen. I hope to get there again sometime!
Excellent ramen! The tsunami (spicy tonkatsu) was my favorite. An excellent ballance of flavors, and the chashu was on point.

This restaurant opened right around the quarantine; now that it is opened again, it deserves all the business it can get. After one excellent lunch, it is now among our favorite Frederick restaurants. The service was exquisite, and the ramen was beatific: a variety of textures and flavors, balanced magnificently. Do yourself a favor and visit or order carry-out!

This new Ramen Restaurant is absolutely amazing!  The inside is decorated with some of the most beautiful asian art you will see in downtown Frederick.  The servers and cook's were very friendly, kind and welcoming.  If you like sweet thai tea's I recommend getting one from here, for me it was a little to sweet but if you got that sweet tooth, it's perfect for you.  The appetizers we had were the chicken Karage (amazing and the sauce was fresh) SeaWeed Salad (Fresh and full of flavor) and the braised short ribs (which was the definition of mouth watery).  For the main dish we both had the Tonkatsu bowl. The noodles you can tell were very fresh, the soup broth was delicious and full of flavor. The only thing I would say is, however which way they cooked their meat, left it just a little bit dry for my taste.  But besides that, all around wonderful, great, experience and I would highly recommend anyone reading this to go check them out!

I ordered curbside pickup for lunch today. Staff were kind enough to run the food out to my car in the alley up the street a bit (thanks Shawn, or Sean?) I got the Tuna Tartare to start and the Red Curry for my main. Delicious! My only critique is I wanted just one more slice of chashu pork with my curry. Not a big deal, because the dish made up for it in a big way with the medium spice broth and a perfect poached egg. I look forward to my next meal from Tsunami!
This place was excellent! Great flavor, great portion sizes and friendly staff. The Bang Bang Shrimp was amazing. And great portions for an appetizer!
Broth is the only thing I enjoyed. Noodles tasted like instant noodles. If I got ramen it would be in DC rather than here. Don’t know what the hype is about.

Got take out. Been looking forward to this place since we moved here. Not very good. It may have been when went at 8pm on a Saturday, but my partner and I couldn’t even eat it.  We both ordered the tonkotsu. Broth had absolutely no flavor. Chashu was dry. The noodles were also dry and didn’t taste right. Not sure if they make their own noodles but it was a first for us to not like the noodles in our ramen which is a big deal. So the three most important ingredients for us were a miss. Especially for the price you’re paying for this ramen. This was one of the more expensive places for ramen that we have been to and it definitely does not live up to that price. The Star was for the shiitake mushrooms which had amazing flavor.  Before we go anywhere we always read the comments and were so excited.  We will stick with getting our ramen elsewhere.

We have been waiting for a Ramen shop to open in Frederick and we were not disappointed. The noodles and vegetables were expertly prepared and the broth was out of this world especially the shiitake mushrooms..... can’t recommend this place enough

We have been several times since they opened! Have only tried a few different ramen and the bang bang shrimp! Everything has always been super delicious. Ingredients taste fresh. The package the ramen for take out with the broth separate so everything at home is just as nice as if you were dining in! The staff always seem friendly and nice. The interior looks great and can’t wait to dine in eventually.
Great and tasty food, I loved the vibes this place has, and the staff members were helpful. I will definitely visit here again.

Really good ramen. I had the spicy miso and it was great. I may ask for extra mushrooms next time instead of the poached egg which had an uncooked texture (I'm sure it was safe, I just dislike runny egg whites).

We've gotten carryout a few times since they've opened (during the pandemic, poor them!) and absolutely everything is scrumptious. The broths are well seasoned and all the ingredients are high quality.  I can't wait to be able to dine in and try their full menu.
Picked up a carryout order yesterday and not only was it delicious, but I was also really impressed by how careful they were being about physical distancing and mask usage.

Great employees and a wonderful interior! Thank you for opening an amazing new taste during this Pandemic. You walk in (limited to 2 at a time) They have everything set up at the front, I called my order in on the way and it was ready! The meals were AMAZING. Had plenty of flavor & spice! yummm I don't eat pork (own beliefs) Absolutely easy to customize, which is a plus! Thank you.

I’m so glad that Ramen place is open in Frederick. The food is outstanding and the vibe on the inside of the restaurant is cool. I’m a big fan of the layout and hopefully they survive this crisis that we’re in right now. Hoping for the best for you all.
Spicy miso is amazing!
DELICIOUS.

It was an exciting treat to have Tsunami open during a difficult time, and the result was fantastic. From first bite to last slurp, the bowl of ramen was delicious. Absolutely worth a pick-up if you have the time.
